            <td class="right">—</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="bold">Market Share</td>
            <td class="right">114.9%</td>
            <td class="right">120.1%</td>
            <td class="right"><span class="kpi-delta delta-down">↓ −5.2%</span></td>
            <td class="right">—</td>
            <td class="right">—</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="total-row">
            <td class="bold">RevPAR Rank</td>
            <td class="right">#2 / 5</td>
            <td class="right">#1 / 5</td>
            <td class="right"><span class="kpi-delta delta-warn">↓ −1</span></td>
            <td class="right">—</td>
            <td class="right">—</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Revenue Manager's Read:</strong> The occupancy index decline (-4.3% vs target) is worth watching. The comp set is filling rooms faster. The Pinch's ADR index (124.0, above the 110.0 target) is the strength — but if occupancy indexing continues to soften into Q2, there is risk of RevPAR index erosion. Monitor pace closely for April through June against comp set pickup rates and be ready to pull tactical occupancy levers if needed.
    </div>

    <!-- SEGMENT ANALYSIS -->
    <div class="section-title" style="font-size:22px; margin-top:36px;">Segment Drilldown — March 2026 vs. March 2025</div>
    <p class="prose" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Year-over-year, the mix shift is significant. OTA non-refundable (TRRTLNREF) became the top segment by revenue contribution — up 5.6 percentage points — while the travel agent flexible segment and the loyalty segment both gave back material volume.</p>

    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table class="data-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Segment</th>
            <th class="right">Rm Nights '26</th>
            <th class="right">ADR '26</th>
            <th class="right">Revenue '26</th>
            <th class="right">Mix %</th>
            <th class="right">Rm Night Δ</th>
            <th class="right">Revenue Δ</th>
