        <h4>Saturday: The High-ADR Day That Lost 20 Room Nights</h4>
        <p>Saturday's ADR rose $92 to $841, but 20 fewer rooms were sold — costing $5,991 in gross revenue. This pattern is the clearest signal of availability restriction impact in the entire dataset. Saturday is typically the highest-demand night for leisure hotels; when Saturday nights are restricted or sold too early, the hotel is leaving its highest-rate opportunities on the table. The vendor's availability exit data (which began March 19) almost certainly skews heavily toward weekend dates. This should be the focal point of any booking engine restriction audit: which Saturday dates were restricted, at what point in the booking window, and were those restrictions pulling rooms back for higher-rate direct channels that never actually materialized?</p>
