      <div class="insight-card opportunity">
        <h4>Midweek is The Pinch's Underappreciated Revenue Story</h4>
        <p>Tuesday and Thursday together added 30 room nights and $23,522 in revenue year-over-year — the largest combined growth of any two-day pairing in the calendar. The ADR gap between Friday ($875) and Tuesday ($534) is $341 — significant, but typical for a leisure-dominant Charleston hotel. What's encouraging is that midweek ADR grew too (+$38 Tuesday, +$28 Thursday), meaning the hotel isn't filling midweek by discounting — it's capturing real demand at improving rates. This midweek strength likely reflects the Charleston corporate and group market, extended leisure stays, and the hotel's growing presence in the "extend the weekend" travel segment. A dedicated midweek package or Tuesday-Thursday minimum stay offer could extend this momentum further into Q2.</p>
