    <div class="section-title">PPC: Misfiring Where It Counts Most</div>

    <div class="prose" style="margin-bottom:24px;">The Pinch is spending roughly $9,200/month on paid search — a figure that represents approximately 2% of room revenue, broadly in line with what a 25-room luxury independent might invest. The budget itself is not the core issue. <strong>The allocation of that budget is.</strong> To evaluate it honestly, the benchmarks need to reflect the reality of operating a boutique property with high brand recognition, an established direct booking base, and an ADR nearly double the Charleston market average. The following analysis uses those property-appropriate standards — not generic platform defaults.</div>

