        <p style="font-size:13px; color:var(--slate-mid); line-height:1.75;">The Performance Max campaign generated 43,537 impressions but only 333 clicks — a 0.76% CTR that signals misaligned audience targeting — and returned a 2.43× ROAS. For a $637 ADR property, that sits below the 4–6× threshold where PMax typically earns its keep for a boutique hotel. PMax does not report keyword-level Quality Scores, which means its efficiency is harder to diagnose than search campaigns. The low CTR and high impression count suggest it is being served to the wrong audiences — possibly broad prospecting that hasn't been given meaningful audience signals to work from. <strong>Recommendation:</strong> Upload a customer match list of past bookers as a primary audience signal, add brand-name searches as exclusions (those should stay in the brand search campaign), and set a 60-day evaluation window. If ROAS remains below 4×, reallocate this $894/month to the proven non-brand search campaigns.</p>
