    <p class="prose" style="margin-bottom:28px;">Entering a high-demand spring shoulder season with strong RevPAR index, growing OTA and consortium volume, and an email channel firing on all cylinders — the fundamentals are in good shape. The following priorities should be actioned before end of April.</p>

    <ul class="priority-list">
      <li class="critical">
        <span class="priority-num">1</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Restructure PPC Allocation — Brand Defense Yes, Brand Dominance No</strong>
          Cap brand search spend at ~35% of total PPC budget (~$3,200/month) — enough to defend against OTA bidding on the property name while maintaining strong impression share. Redirect the freed budget into the Non-Brand Hotel and Non-Brand Luxury campaigns, which are currently generating 8–11× ROAS on a shoestring. Pause the Non-Brand Best/Charleston campaign pending a full conversion path audit — it drove 317 clicks and zero revenue. Optimize or replace the Performance Max campaign, which is returning a subpar 2.43× ROAS. The conservatively projected upside from reallocation alone is $15,000–$30,000 in additional monthly revenue from net-new guests.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="critical">
        <span class="priority-num">2</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Diagnose and Recover the TRLOYALTY Segment</strong>
          A 64% drop in loyalty room nights (−57 nights, −$26,958) is the most urgent revenue issue on the property. Identify whether this is a rate plan distribution issue, an awareness failure, or an uncompetitive offer. Evaluate the "Insider Pay Now and Save" plan's positioning versus OTA flexible rates and consider a targeted loyalty win-back campaign through direct channels. This segment should be restored to 60–80 nights in Q2.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="important">
        <span class="priority-num">6</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Scale Email Marketing — The Highest-Converting Channel</strong>
          Email converted at 9.6% — roughly 16× the site average — with $11,910 in revenue and $143 ARPU from just 83 first-user sessions (HubSpot attribution). ChatGPT referrals generated 7.7% CVR and $1,937 from 13 sessions — an emerging channel to watch. The email program is the most capital-efficient channel in the portfolio. Invest in list growth now: at $143 ARPU, adding 200 qualified subscribers could generate ~$28,600 in additional direct revenue per campaign cycle. Develop a list-building strategy (on-property capture, post-stay outreach, booking engine opt-in) and test segmented offers for April and May advance purchase windows.
